WEBVTT

00:00.471 --> 00:01.505
<i>My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.528 --> 00:07.063
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.131 --> 00:09.499
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing --</i>

00:09.567 --> 00:12.068
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:12.136 --> 00:14.404
<i>You're stuck in whatever city</i>
<i>they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:14.472 --> 00:16.573
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:16.640 --> 00:19.809
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:19.877 --> 00:22.445
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:22.513 --> 00:24.047
<i>A trigger-happy</i>
<i>ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.115 --> 00:25.682
Should we shoot them?

00:25.750 --> 00:28.251
<i>...An old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.319 --> 00:30.653
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:30.721 --> 00:33.123
<i>...Family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.190 --> 00:35.358
<i>...If you're desperate.</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.426 --> 00:37.861
<i>Bottom line --</i>
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:37.928 --> 00:39.529
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:45.702 --> 00:46.825
<i>For spies,</i>

00:46.826 --> 00:49.427
<i>top-secret clearance</i>
<i>is just the beginning.</i>

00:49.495 --> 00:51.429
<i>S.C.I. --</i>
<i>The right to view</i>

00:51.497 --> 00:53.365
<i>sensitive compartmentalized</i>
<i>information --</i>

00:53.432 --> 00:55.066
<i>is reserved</i>

00:55.134 --> 00:58.236
<i>for the most trusted people</i>
<i>in the intelligence community.</i>

00:58.304 --> 01:00.572
That kind of access
comes with fewer constraints,

01:00.640 --> 01:02.073
<i>limited oversight,</i>

01:02.141 --> 01:05.343
<i>and a frightening ability</i>
<i>to do real harm.</i>

01:12.485 --> 01:15.053
I'm getting a little jealous
of that badge.

01:15.121 --> 01:18.523
I remember when you couldn't
keep your hands off me.

01:18.591 --> 01:20.892
I've waited years to see my name
on this again.

01:20.960 --> 01:22.694
Now that it finally is...

01:22.762 --> 01:25.730
A psychopath blackmails you
into using it

01:25.798 --> 01:28.667
to destroy files
in the CIA's computer system.

01:28.734 --> 01:31.403
And when I do this,

01:31.470 --> 01:34.806
Anson Fullerton
goes back to being a ghost.

01:34.874 --> 01:36.808
I don't want you doing anything
for that man.

01:36.876 --> 01:38.677
If I don't do this, Fi,
you'll spend

01:38.744 --> 01:41.580
the rest of your life in jail
for something you didn't do.

01:41.647 --> 01:44.816
You think he's just gonna hand
over the evidence he has on me?

01:44.884 --> 01:46.251
He'll keep forcing you
to do his bidding.

01:46.319 --> 01:49.154
There is no end to this.
That is a possibility,

01:49.222 --> 01:51.456
but right now,
I don't have much choice.

01:51.524 --> 01:54.059
Well, I'm not willing
to throw in the towel yet.

01:54.126 --> 01:56.995
Can you call Anson,
tell him you need to meet?

01:57.063 --> 01:58.330
For what?

01:58.397 --> 02:00.966
Make up a reason.

02:01.033 --> 02:02.801
But if you can get him
away from his car,

02:02.869 --> 02:04.970
Sam and I can plant
this tracker.

02:05.037 --> 02:07.405
We can follow the rat
back to his nest.

02:07.473 --> 02:10.208
Anson's not gonna hide blackmail
material under his pillow.

02:10.276 --> 02:11.776
Well, maybe we get lucky
and he does.

02:11.844 --> 02:13.311
It's too risky
for a "maybe."

02:13.379 --> 02:14.746
It's even riskier
to do nothing.

02:14.814 --> 02:16.815
We can't win
if we don't play.

02:20.086 --> 02:22.454
18 bucks for a mojito?

02:22.521 --> 02:24.623
What kind of a tourist trap
is this?

02:24.690 --> 02:27.259
A tourist trap with a good view
of Michael's meeting place.

02:27.326 --> 02:29.461
You're wishing that
was a sniper rifle, aren't you?

02:29.528 --> 02:31.897
Can you think of anyone

02:31.964 --> 02:34.366
who deserves a bullet
more than that soulless bastard?

02:34.433 --> 02:36.701
Well, for now, let's just stick
to finding out where he lives.

02:36.769 --> 02:39.404
Okay, here he comes.

02:39.472 --> 02:41.473
Break a leg, Fi.

02:43.476 --> 02:46.611
Michael,
you look tired.

02:46.679 --> 02:50.148
Laboring on my behalf,
I presume?

02:50.216 --> 02:52.117
We better walk and talk.
Can I buy you a lemonade?

02:58.824 --> 03:00.392
You haven't answered
my question.

03:00.459 --> 03:01.893
There's a little delay.

03:01.961 --> 03:03.194
A delay?

03:03.262 --> 03:04.496
You have official access

03:04.563 --> 03:06.932
and the tools
to erase my name from that file.

03:06.999 --> 03:09.434
- Why isn't it done?
- Clearance is being held up.

03:09.502 --> 03:11.236
- It shouldn't be long, but --
- No.

03:11.304 --> 03:12.504
What do you mean, "no"?

03:12.571 --> 03:15.140
There's a great sentence
in your psych eval.

03:15.207 --> 03:18.743
It says, "Westen is particularly
skilled at social engineering,

03:18.811 --> 03:20.745
"creating rapport
with targets

03:20.813 --> 03:22.914
and steering them
towards an objective."

03:22.982 --> 03:24.716
I know your moves
better than you do.

03:24.784 --> 03:26.151
I don't know
what you're planning,

03:26.218 --> 03:28.086
but I'm not
going to fall for it.

03:32.858 --> 03:35.727
I can't see them.
Am I clear?

03:36.929 --> 03:39.331
We're good. Mike walked
Anson out to the dunes, so...

03:39.398 --> 03:41.833
Yeah, go for it.

03:41.901 --> 03:43.668
Friday.

03:43.736 --> 03:45.904
Have my name erased
from those files by Friday,

03:45.972 --> 03:48.173
or Fiona gets used
to taking group showers.

03:53.379 --> 03:55.313
Hang on, Fi. He's turned around.
Get out of there.

03:55.381 --> 03:56.815
No. There's still
a way to do this.

04:02.688 --> 04:03.998
He's headed to the bridge.

04:04.023 --> 04:05.383
He's gonna have to cross
the light at Collins.

04:05.391 --> 04:06.558
I'll catch him there.

